</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utgbarton.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tgbarton</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/22/01 6:10:21 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Intentions</span><hr size=1> I don't think the issue is one of definitions, but one of conduct.  Obviously, Verant has not built a reservation system into EverQuest.  Therefore, by default, there can only be intentions.  However, that doesn't mean that we, the players, can't treat those intentions like reservations.  <br>
<br>
It sounds like some players respect intentions as if they were reservations.  Others treat postings to the raid intentions forum as mere recruiting calls; if you want to show up at a spawn before, or even the same time as, another group, then go for it.  Is that latter situation really what we want on Brell?<br>
<br>
Is there some set of standards that Brell players have adopted in the past that we need to be reminded of (I couldn't find them, so please enlighten me if you know of them)?  If not, let's use this thread to define a set of standards.  Here are some criteria to consider so that we don't turn into a chaotic FFA server:<br>
<br>
An intention should be treated as a virtual reservation when some or all of the following are true:<br>
*  The mob spawns longer than a certain time period (2 hours?  4 hours? etc.).<br>
*  A combined level total of XXX is generally required to take down, or reach, the mob.<br>
*  An extremely rare/epic quest/no drop/etc. item drops from the mob.<br>
<br>
There are probably more criteria that should be considered.  Please suggest some.  Also, please comment on how virtual reservations can be made and honored.  Obviously, first-come-first-served is the best, but should there also be a requirement that the posting person have an adequate group formed before the intention becomes a reservation?  That would allow multiple people to post intentions and then the first to have the requisite number of people sign on (in the forum) gets the reservation.<br>
<br>
Or am I totally out-of-touch with everyone and can I start organizing a Plane of Air raid without regard of anyone else's intentions?  If so, please be sure to post when you're planning on raiding Air so I can be sure to get my group there before you do...<br>
<br>
- Hydrak Daishofist<br>
Art of War <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uberrymoorvontrapp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Berrymoor vonTrapp</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#CC9900>(1/22/01 6:49:49 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Well..</span><hr size=1> /agree<br>
